# Introduction

R Markdown is a powerful tool that allows users to combine narrative text, code, and output into a single document. It is widely used in data science because it supports reproducibility, meaning others can run the same code and obtain the same results. By integrating Markdown formatting, R code chunks, and LaTeX math, R Markdown provides a flexible and efficient way to present analyses.

# Narrative Section

One of the biggest advantages of R Markdown is its ability to seamlessly blend explanation and computation. Instead of writing code separately and copying results into a report, everything exists in one place. This reduces errors and improves clarity. It also makes collaboration easier, as others can follow both the logic and the results step by step.

